* ~~leanprover-community/mathlib4#10377~~
* ~~leanprover-community/mathlib4#11244~~
By **[Dependent Issues](https://github.com/z0al/dependent-issues)** (🤖). Happy coding!
<!-- By Dependent Issues (Action) - DO NOT REMOVE -->
I'm not sure if there is a more general version of `MDifferentiable_iff_extension_DifferentiableOn` that we might want to add. I experimented with this, but couldn't quite get the setup right.
I ran `lake exe shake --update` but I don't know if I should have, I'll wait for an expert to say if this is ok.
No, that's the wrong thing: you should revert your changes to `noshake.json` and run `lake exe shake --fix` instead.

> No, that's the wrong thing: you should revert your changes to `noshake.json` and run `lake exe shake --fix` instead.

I did that originally, but the fix meant a file wouldn't compile, so I went for the update route.

That's weird. If `lake exe shake --fix` is giving wrong results, I suggest that you restore the branch to the state it was in before you started the tree-shaking, and then report on zulip that the script is giving misleading output on this branch.
I have done some digging and I know what's causing this. Shall I push my fix?

> I have done some digging and I know what's causing this. Shall I push my fix?

Sure it seems it doesn't like the file where the notation is defined. I guess one solution is to move the notation from ../Manifold to ../Topology?

Not quite. The issue is that `notation` declarations are visible to the parser, but invisible to `shake` (which only notices when the notation is _used_, not when it's defined). 

I suggest the following in `UpperHalfPlane.Topology`:
- add the `PartialHomeomorph` import
- add the following definition:
  ```lean
  /-- A continuous section `ℂ → ℍ` of the natural inclusion map, bundled as a `PartialHomeomorph`. -/
  def ofComplex : PartialHomeomorph ℂ ℍ := (openEmbedding_coe.toPartialHomeomorph _).symm
  
  /-- Extend a function on `ℍ` arbitrarily to a function on all of `ℂ`. -/
  scoped[UpperHalfPlane] notation "↑ₕ" f => f ∘ ofComplex
  ```
Then `shake` won't complain, because it sees the `def` and accepts that as a reason to import `PartialHomeomorph`. I think it's useful anyway to give the section of the inclusion map a name: then we can formulate a lemma that it's continuous or mdifferentiable, etc.
Looks good to me now. If you're happy with it, please label with "awaiting review" and "awaiting CI", and I'll flag it for merging if the CI run passes.
done!

(which raises the question of whether this lemma is needed at all)
Yes with the other changes I no longer need this lemma.

```suggestion
/-- Eisenstein series are MDifferentiable (i.e. holomorphic functions from `ℍ → ℂ`). -/
theorem eisensteinSeries_SIF_MDifferentiable {k : ℤ} {N : ℕ} (hk : 3 ≤ k) (a : Fin 2 → ZMod N) :
    MDifferentiable 𝓘(ℂ) 𝓘(ℂ) (eisensteinSeries_SIF a k) := by
  rw [MDifferentiable_iff_extension_DifferentiableOn]
  exact (eisensteinSeries_tendstoLocallyUniformlyOn hk a).differentiableOn 
    (eventually_of_forall fun s ↦ DifferentiableOn.sum 
      fun _ _ ↦ eisSummad_extension_differentiableOn _ _) 
    (isOpen_lt continuous_const continuous_im)
```

```suggestion
      exact fun z hz ↦ linear_ne_zero _ ⟨z, hz⟩
```

```suggestion
        ((comp_ne_zero_iff _ Int.cast_injective Int.cast_zero).mpr ha)
```
(& again 2 lines down)

```suggestion
    · exact fun z hz ↦ zpow_ne_zero k (linear_ne_zero (a ·)
```

```suggestion
    DifferentiableOn ℂ (↑ₕf) {z : ℂ | 0 < z.im} := by
```
I'm surprised this is so painful. The comparable argument for Jacobi theta functions (in JacobiTheta.Manifold) is literally a one-liner, why doesn't the same work here?

PS. Here is an alternative argument.

Firstly, add the following API lemma for the "↑ₕ" operator:
```lean
lemma extends_def (f : ℍ → ℂ) (z : ℍ) : 
    (↑ₕ f) z.1 = f z := by
  have := PartialHomeomorph.left_inv (PartialHomeomorph.symm
    (OpenEmbedding.toPartialHomeomorph UpperHalfPlane.coe openEmbedding_coe)) (x := z.1) ?_
  · simp only [Function.comp_apply]
    congr 1
    ext
    simpa only [PartialHomeomorph.symm_symm, OpenEmbedding.toPartialHomeomorph_apply,
      UpperHalfPlane.coe] using this
  · simp only [PartialHomeomorph.symm_toPartialEquiv, PartialEquiv.symm_source,
       OpenEmbedding.toPartialHomeomorph_target, mem_range]
    exists z
```
This can, incidentally, be used to golf the proof of `eisSummand_extension_differentiableOn` considerably, so it more or less "pays for itself".

Then change the proof of `eisensteinSeries_SIF_MDifferentiable` to the following:
```lean
theorem eisensteinSeries_SIF_MDifferentiable {k : ℤ} {N : ℕ} (hk : 3 ≤ k) (a : Fin 2 → ZMod N) :
    MDifferentiable 𝓘(ℂ) 𝓘(ℂ) (eisensteinSeries_SIF a k) := by
  intro τ
  suffices DifferentiableAt ℂ (↑ₕeisensteinSeries_SIF a k) τ.1 by
    convert MDifferentiableAt.comp τ (DifferentiableAt.mdifferentiableAt this) τ.mdifferentiable_coe
    exact funext fun z ↦ (extends_def (eisensteinSeries_SIF a k) z).symm
  refine DifferentiableOn.differentiableAt ?_ 
    ((isOpen_lt continuous_const Complex.continuous_im).mem_nhds τ.2)
  exact (eisensteinSeries_tendstoLocallyUniformlyOn hk a).differentiableOn
    (eventually_of_forall fun s ↦ DifferentiableOn.sum
      fun _ _ ↦ eisSummand_extension_differentiableOn _ _)
    (isOpen_lt continuous_const continuous_im)
```
Ah I didn't know about `DifferentiableAt.mdifferentiableAt` which is the key here, this way I don't need that other ugly lemma which I was wondering about. I'll incorporate this and try again.
Are the changes to this file intentional, or just a git glitch?
No this was just a glitch same below I think
Same comment as above: are the changes to this file intentional, or just a git glitch? (Everything compiles without them.)

You're already in namespace `UpperHalfPlane` so you don't need the explciit namespace name
```suggestion
scoped notation "↑ₕ" f => f ∘ ofComplex
```

This proof is clumsy, and the name is not good (both my fault, sorry). Much better:
```suggestion
lemma ofComplex_apply (z : ℍ) : ofComplex (z : ℂ) = z := 
  OpenEmbedding.toPartialHomeomorph_left_inv ..

lemma comp_ofComplex (f : ℍ → ℂ) (z : ℍ) : (↑ₕ f) z = f z := by
  rw [Function.comp_apply, ofComplex_apply]
```

```suggestion
  apply comp_ofComplex
```

```suggestion
    exact funext fun z ↦ (comp_ofComplex (eisensteinSeries_SIF a k) z).symm
```
a git glitch that slipped through the net
